\lim_{x\to0}\ x^2\left(1+2+3+...+\left[\frac1{|x|}\right]\right)
\vert x \vert \in \left(\dfrac1{n+1}, \dfrac1n\right]
\lfloor 1/\vert x \vert \rfloor = n
n \to \infty
\vert x \vert \to 0
1/2
1 + 2 + 3 + \cdots + \cdots + n = \dfrac{n(n+1)}2
1 + 2 + 3 + \cdots + \cdots + \lfloor 1/\vert x \vert \rfloor = \dfrac{\lfloor 1/\vert x \vert \rfloor(\lfloor 1/\vert x \vert \rfloor+1)}2 = \dfrac{n(n+1)}2
x^2 \left(1 + 2 + 3 + \cdots + \cdots + \lfloor 1/\vert x \vert \rfloor \right) = \dfrac{x^2n(n+1)}2 \in \left(\dfrac{n}{2(n+1)}, \dfrac{n+1}{2n} \right]
